paragraphs.text: 8 months later, I’ve watched maybe an hour of your content. But the company I run sales at is killing it and the rest of my life “marriage, fatherhood, friends” is in a much better place.
paragraphs.name: c0bb
6b3a
paragraphs.text: Then it hit me. Fuck it. I’m a sales leader, not an entrepreneur. I LOVE sales. I had spent five years helping grow a business from 1–50m a year in net new sales. I wanted more. So I pushed my chips in, all of them. Inspired by the Daily V and seeing how hard you went I scheduled a blitz trip to Austin. 36 hours, 5 meetings, 2 dinners, one happy hour, $150 bucks in Uber fairs. 3 job offers.

paragraphs.name: 3d90
paragraphs.text: I’m not coming to your SXSW keynote, even though it’s a 5 min walk from my office. Frankly, it’s not the best use of my time and money.
